Returns: The state key that was loaded.

ClassDesc: Result retrieved from @B_com#google#android#gms#appstate#AppStateManager#StateResult_E@ when app state data has been loaded successfully. Possible status codes include: @B_com#google#android#gms#appstate#AppStateStatusCodes#STATUS_OK_E@ if data was successfully loaded and is up-to-date. @B_com#google#android#gms#appstate#AppStateStatusCodes#STATUS_NETWORK_ERROR_NO_DATA_E@ if the device was unable to communicate with the network and has no local data available. @B_com#google#android#gms#appstate#AppStateStatusCodes#STATUS_NETWORK_ERROR_STALE_DATA_E@ if the device was unable to retrieve the latest data from the network. @B_com#google#android#gms#appstate#AppStateStatusCodes#STATUS_CLIENT_RECONNECT_REQUIRED_E@ if the client needs to reconnect to the service to access this data. @B_com#google#android#gms#appstate#AppStateStatusCodes#STATUS_INTERNAL_ERROR_E@ if an unexpected error occurred in the service. @B_com#google#android#gms#appstate#AppStateStatusCodes#STATUS_STATE_KEY_NOT_FOUND_E@ if the requested state key is not found on the server. @B_com#google#android#gms#appstate#AppStateStatusCodes#STATUS_STATE_KEY_LIMIT_EXCEEDED_E@ if the application already has data present in the maximum number of state keys.
